'''Columella''' (in plants) is an axis of sterile tissue which passes through the center of the spore-case of [[moss]]es.<ref>{{NSRW|wstitle=Columella |inline=1}}</ref>

The term '''columella''' is also used to refer to story 1 to story 4 (S1 - S4) cells in the root cap located apically of the quiescent centre. In fungi it refers to central vacuolated part in hyphae.


